               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210912-200-person1972">
                  WILLIAM 
                  RIVERS NASH
               <interp inst="t18210912-200-person1972" type="surname" value="RIVERS NASH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210912-200-person1972" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210912-200-person1972" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was servant to the prosecutors. On the 11th of September, the prisoner was <rs id="t18210912-200-deflabel1173" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-200-defend1965 t18210912-200-deflabel1173"></join> to the house. I had suspicions and missed a shilling. I took him up stairs and told him, I suspected him. I left him in the room, and on returning, I found a duplicate partly torn on the ground, and part in his hand, but before I attempted to pick it up, he had torn it all. I took it off the ground, and by it I found the silk shawl at Wood's. I found the other property at the Grafton Arms, public-house, Grafton-street; he told me he had left a bundle there - I went and found it, and gave it to the head-borough.</p>
               <p>
            
